The proper tool for extracting substrings matching a regexp from a command&#39;s output is `grep`. Like,
```
echo &quot;Test12h&quot; | grep -o &#39;^[^[:digit:]]*&#39;
```
will output `Test`.

If `Test12h` is in a variable, you don&#39;t even need external utilies; parameter expansions can easily handle that, e.g:
```
var=&#39;Test12h&#39;
