- By default, MyBatis uses [`EnumTypeHandler`](https://github.com/mybatis/mybatis-3/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/ibatis/type/EnumTypeHandler.java) which calls `name()` method when binding enum parameters. You need to tell MyBatis to use [`EnumOrdinalTypeHandler`](https://github.com/mybatis/mybatis-3/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/ibatis/type/EnumOrdinalTypeHandler.java) instead.
- You should use `#{}` instead of `${}` whenever possible. See the [FAQ](https://github.com/mybatis/mybatis-3/wiki/FAQ#what-is-the-difference-between--and-).

```xml
&lt;if test=&quot;array!= null and array.length &gt; 0&quot;&gt;
  AND arrayValCol IN
  &lt;foreach item=&quot;item&quot; collection=&quot;array&quot; separator=&quot;,&quot; open=&quot;(&quot; close=&quot;)&quot;&gt;
    #{item,typeHandler=org.apache.ibatis.type.EnumOrdinalTypeHandler}
  &lt;/foreach&gt;
&lt;/if&gt;
```

It is also possible to change the default enum type handler by specifying [`defaultEnumTypeHandler`](https://mybatis.org/mybatis-3/configuration.html#settings) in configuration.

```xml
&lt;settings&gt;
  &lt;setting name=&quot;defaultEnumTypeHandler&quot;
    value=&quot;org.apache.ibatis.type.EnumOrdinalTypeHandler&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/settings&gt;
```

